##I cried for a hospital bed

Southreviews

Functional presentation, the power of calm

"everyone is so ridiculous, " Ms. Cai said

On the afternoon of Feb. 5, Cai stood in line for three hours at the crowded outpatient department of the Hubei Provincial People's Hospital. COVID-19,43, and her mother were among 1,500 nucleic acid tests performed at the hospital yesterday. Now, Cai Ting all heart above, all heart hope it is positive.

"I was really looking forward to getting a new case of coronary pneumonia and proving that I was sick just in case it came back negative. "

A few hours later, Cai Ting sent me the diagnosis: mother, Shan Yang, still one positive indicator away from the diagnosis. Is still highly suspect. And she's negative on both of her own markers.

This may be a good result, on common sense. But the normally upbeat Cai Ting told me that she broke down and "burst into tears in the hospital" but was unable to breathe and knew that something was clearly wrong with her lungs. And the mother has been unable to move, had to push a wheelchair by her, in the inch-long walk in Wuhan, back and forth. Under the circumstances, do a review, rushed to say, there is no way to predict when can be cured.

The Wuhan patients have more enemies to overcome than they have to overcome their diseases.

Battle stations
As early as January 22, Cai Ting sent out a message asking for help on her friends'circle.

Cai Ting's sister-in-law in the Hubei Province People's hospital treatment of gynecological tumors, there are signs of fever, fever clinic at the beginning of the hospital did not receive, and can not provide transfer assistance, only to discharge. No nurse would dare to do PICC, which is vital for patients undergoing chemotherapy.

The results of the examination showed that the index highly suspected new coronary pneumonia, the next day was sent to the isolation ward, and then transferred to the ninth people's Hospital in Wuhan. At the same time, close care of Aunt Cai Ting for more than half a month, also developed a high fever, all the way up to 39.

At this time, the epidemic in Hubei has spread, Wuhan medical resources shortage up. She called 120, but was told she had to contact the hospital and emergency services to send a car. Cai Ting thought of the situation of Aunt, himself as a close contact, asked to enter Wuhan Nine hospital to do the inspection.

After consultation, the hospital agreed to her request, January 23 This Day, emergency vehicles from noon to night, finally at 9 o'clock in the evening to send her to the nine hospitals. All night. She walked out of the hospital at 5:00 a.m. , and the C.T. and blood work came back normal, but we don't rule out an incubation period.

Cai Ting was admitted to hospital with her first fever

For days after that, Cai ting was in combat mode. Both she and her mother had recurrent fevers, and her mother became so weak that she could hardly walk. At 5 a.m. on Feb. 1, Cai Ting, who had a fever of 38.5, called 120. 20 minutes later, the car arrived. But the staff told them that they could not deliver the patients without contacting the hospital and the beds. She had to get out of the car.
On February 2, Cai Ting's CT report showed a diagnosis of new coronary pneumonia. At this time, the mother's CT results also showed that the lungs have been hoary. The diagnosis was double lung infection. Consider neocoronary pneumonia. The doctor told her sympathetically that she would have to wait two days to see if there was a bed, and that she had not had a new patient for a week. At this point, the mother has been unable to walk, can not stand for a long time, she asked for help, only to buy a wheelchair.

Hospital records for Cai Ting's mother

I arranged interviews with her, repeatedly interrupted by various unexpected, has not been able to carry out, I can only watch her circle of friends announced how he solved a "super impossible task. ".

On the evening of Feb. 3, Cai Ting was awakened by a cold sensation at home. She found her body on the ground, her face swollen and covered with blood. I peed my pants.

She realized she had fainted, but she didn't know how long. She called 911, but she didn't make a sound. Fortunately, acquaintances and strangers online helped her connect with the community's motorcade. In the Light Valley Hospital District of Wuhan Third Hospital, Cai Ting can not stand, cold sweat, feeling to shock. Probably all the medical resources and energy were devoted to the fever, which made it impossible to deal with the trauma, and there was a waiting list for emergency treatment.

At the door of the emergency room she heard a mournful cry in a great silence, and in the emergency room the faintest inhalations could be heard.

Wuhan University Zhongnan Hospital Intensive Care Isolation Ward

The doctor told her that this shock, may be caused by high fever, but there is no bed, and it is already 11 o'clock in the night, the hospital disinfection, injections still need to wait a few hours, paid the money of Cai Ting, also had to give up.
There's only one way to find out. Run a nucleic acid test to confirm. She had planned to take her mother the next day in a wheelchair, but now she didn't have the strength to cry.

February 4, after many twists and turns, she took her mother to the Provincial People's hospital for a nucleic acid test, got a seemingly gratifying result, but made her "collapse. ".

The only access to the ward
For more than 10 days, nucleic acid testing has been the only evidence of access to the ward for a large number of people seeking help. Patients who have not been diagnosed by nucleic acid testing can only wait. Applying for a nucleic acid test was a time-consuming and time-consuming battle. As of Feb. 7, there were more than 1,100 requests for help from "pneumonia patients" on Weibo, most of them related to nucleic acid testing.

Chen Qi, a 20-year-old girl, was one of them. She had just learned how to drive a battery-powered car. She was carrying her father, who was coughing, to all the hospitals and kept alive with injections. Father from the New Year 30 began to have fever symptoms, the last three days, father began to cough up blood, has been out of breath, high fever once more than 40 degrees.

They were given a slot for nucleic acid testing at the seventh Wuhan Hospital, but it would take three days to test and four days to get results. Chen Qi and his family panicked, feeling that his father will not live through tomorrow, simply can not wait.

Wuhan implemented grid management, fever patients reported to the community, layer upon layer coordination, and sent to the designated hospitals for treatment. But the response from the community was mostly, "be patient. ". On February 2, his father saw no way out, Chen Qi's sister and mother in the community and street a row, the street would send them to the river across the concord hospital for nucleic acid testing.

"They got my dad a rescue car, but my dad was infected and the family had to sit outside the car like stowaways. "

Wuhan Huoshenshan Hospital, medical staff to patients into the ward

Chen Qi's father has not been what disease, do not smoke and do not drink, is the only pillar of the family, has a fearless character. He barely put on his mask when he started vomiting on the first day of the New Year. But the illness seemed to take him down, and he became emotionally unstable, unwilling to remember how he caught the virus.

Now, it's been 48 hours since the inspection, and the family is a little upset that the notice didn't come. Chen Qi said: "Now the whole country, are in the treatment of new coronary pneumonia, if my father does not have this disease, at this juncture, then no one care. So my father is not saved? "

The CDC finally called on Feb. 4 to confirm the diagnosis and report it. Chen Qi this just a little bit relieved: saved.

Xu's mother-in-law, Chen Hui, is much luckier than the twists and turns of nucleic acid testing in most patients.

Xu's mother in law had a second CT scan during the day on Feb. 4, and her lungs were completely vitrified. Doctors stopped her Moxifloxacin injection and said it was useless, except for in hospital playing Globulin.

This led to a vicious circle: only the hospital department had access to the protein, and the hospital department said that only the outbreak command could allocate beds, and only the community could report the allocation of beds. But the community tells them to be patient.

A sense of hopelessness pervades. In the video, Chen Hui can still joke with her grandson at first, but recently she has become more and more depressed. Mother-in-law can understand the lung, mouth with "faith destiny" , do not want to run again.

In desperation, the family had to buy their own Globulin. On the night of February 4th they went to Puren hospital to see if they could get their Ivig, and the answer was as expected: No. Unexpectedly, the doctor told me that 80 kits had arrived that afternoon, a temporary addition.

On February 2, Wuhan issued a new policy calling for the "four categories" of people diagnosed with NCP, suspected, feverish and close contacts to be treated and quarantined. The next day, a community worker sent her a message asking her mother-in-law if she wanted to go to quarantine, but when she saw that the quarantine did not provide medical care, she gave up and was afraid.

What granny needs is help. She needs a shot of Globulin. Now we're counting on that NUCLEIC ACID test. Worryingly, 48 hours later, the test results are still not available. And right now, for the patient, every minute is a matter of life and death.

What you can and can't get
On Feb. 4, my father called Hao and told her about the results of her nucleic acid test. Hear"negative"this word, Hao Ming in the heart a cool: finished, completely finished.

The Grandmother, 78, who had been on dialysis for three years, developed a fever in December and was diagnosed with pneumonia. Infection did not see good, but the fever subsided, until the new virus in Wuhan outbreak, then to the South Hospital CT, the lungs have been seriously infected. The doctors suspected Covid-19, told them to go home and wait for the call, and stopped the grandmother's dialysis.

On February 4th the dialysis she was supposed to undergo failed, and her condition deteriorated rapidly. They found Liyuan hospital, did a nucleic acid test, the results were negative. With the report in hand, Hao and his family returned to COVID-19 to prove that the grandmother was not contagious and could continue dialysis. However, doctors concluded that this is the new coronary pneumonia, NUCLEIC ACID test accuracy is not high, to the designated hospital in Wuhan No. 7 re-testing.

At this point, the grandmother fell into shock, the sound and shake of the loss of response, people can not eat, not to do nucleic acid review. They called 120 three times and were told they would not be able to send a car unless they contacted a hospital willing to treat them. But the general hospital does not dare to admit, Wuhan four designated hospitals to the fever dialysis patient, all needs the nucleic acid test diagnosis to be able to admit.

"The vast majority of medical resources and beds in Wuhan are focused on new coronary pneumonia. If it is negative, basically no one will care. "

Hao Ming's grandmother has been lying at home like this.

A day earlier, on the afternoon of February 5, the National Health and Human Services Commission issued the fifth edition of the diagnostic and treatment plan for COVID-19 pneumonia, which stipulates that CT findings should be used as the diagnostic criteria for clinical cases (only in Hubei Province) , this means that the only standard for nucleic acid testing is over. That said, under this plan, Hao's grandmother will be treated, but whether medical resources can keep up may be another matter.

The doctor is looking at the CT scan of the patient's lung

After Peng Yuxian in Hanyang District posted her grandmother's appeal online, she was contacted by a staff member who claimed to be a local public opinion network, who informed her of the new state-issued document that serious suspected patients would also be treated. You can go if you have a bed, but you can't go if you don't have one.

Peng Yuxian's grandmother had a serious lung infection, but the nucleic acid test result was negative. Her mother and herself were isolated. As the grandmother of a negative patient, all kinds of chronic diseases were caused by pneumonia, and she cried at home all day about her heart pain, and so did the whole family.

On February 4th both the mother and herself tested positive for nucleic acids. It's confirmed. MOM's in critical condition, breathing hard, can't move, says a word or two, breathes hard. According to the CT scan, the mother's lung albinism had progressed to a severe form, and she was admitted to Wuhan's Fifth Hospital.

For Peng Yuxian, the diagnosis, is a long known results, finally got the medical recognition. A family from January 20, began to appear symptoms, the mother is the first patient, followed by grandmother, there is no bed, only home isolation. Are those who are loved and cared for more than their own safety. "Is not the professional, the safeguard measure does not do adequately" , the family interior aggregation infection, has become an inevitable situation.

Peng Yuxian symptoms January 26,28 to CT, lungs have ground glass, but she is in good health, the doctor also advised her, first home isolation. During the period, the disease has been repeated, and sometimes improved.

The night after the diagnosis, that is, the night of February 5, Peng Yuxian just lay down, there was a phone call, said, within an hour to pick you up to quarantine. A little after 1 a.m. , she packed up, got on the bus, was taken to a gathering point in Hanyang District, waited for other patients, and was transferred by a bus to the Shelter Hospital at the Wuhan Exhibition Center.

It was empty, boarded up and divided into large wards. At 3:00, she was assigned to Ward 5. A ward has 20 beds, separated by half a meter or so distance, here the isolation of the main patients with mild illness, but also have cough.

Kong Hon Shelter Hospital

On the way, it was raining, Peng Yuxian took the window of the car, made a friend circle: on the way, get a known result, but will be relatively relieved a lot.

But when it came to her grandmother, who was in her 80s, she choked up and choked up. After the quarantine, there was nothing she could do. She could only wait for the good news from her uncle and father.

"South Wind Window" reporter as a rescue team volunteers, since February 4, began to interview Chen Qi, Xu Min, Hao Ming, such as help, and try to help them connect to the medical resources. The good news is that the shortage of beds is being alleviated with the completion and commissioning of Vulcan Mountain, Raytheon Mountain, and other large rectangular hospitals.

Unfortunately, sometimes the phone rings and before you can ask if the problem has been solved, the person says, probably not. Clearly, some of the patients were not outpacing the pace. Some hung up in silence, others cursed in anger.

Early in the morning of February 6, Hao Ming sent me a message: the Local Health Commission told us that the hospital list has been opened, the next day can be hospitalized.

Finally he said, "it's too bad grandma can't wait. "

On the third day, Xu's mother in law, Chen Hui, was finally diagnosed. They were expecting positive nucleic acid test results, but unfortunately, the 60 year old mother in law, still couldn't wait for a bed, xu Min announced the news of her mother-in-law's death in the afternoon in the circle of friends.

So is the good news. On the evening of February 6, Cai Ting shared the good news with me. That day, she spoke to her aunt on the phone. Her voice was as healthy as it had been before chemotherapy. Her sister-in-law, a cancer patient on chemotherapy, appears to have recovered from a severe immune deficiency. At present, the aunt has done a nucleic acid test, the result is negative, if the second test is negative, can be discharged from the hospital, just a week in isolation, can go home.

On the other hand, although Cai Ting's mother is only a highly suspected single Yang patient, according to the latest diagnosis and treatment program, this situation can also be reported to the hospital. On the afternoon of the 6th, in the rain and without a car, she pushed her wheelchair for more than an hour, finally pushing her 69-year-old mother into the hospital.

She returned home, exhausted, ready to rest and return to the fight.

This just in
The shortage of medical supplies and the difficulty of testing and diagnosis are being alleviated.

These days, the Vulcan Mountain, Raytheon Mountain Hospital and shelter have been put into use, intensive treatment of severe, mild patients. Fire Mountain Hospital has been officially admitted to treat patients with newly diagnosed pneumonia since February 4. Today, four days later, the hospital has also been put into use. The first medical team has been stationed in the hospital, and patients will start receiving treatment today. The two special hospitals have a total of 2,500 beds.

Starting from the evening of February 3, medical rescue teams from 20 large-scale Tertiary General Hospitals in 20 provinces were urgently dispatched to Transform 13 stadium and convention and Exhibition Centers in Wuhan into "Shelter Hospitals" , for the treatment of new patients with mild coronary pneumonia. At present, Wuhan Convention and Exhibition Center, Wembley Arena, Wuhan Living Room construction of the three shelter hospitals, gradually put into use.

For some patients with fever due to objective reasons can not be confirmed, it is difficult to get effective isolation and treatment of the situation, Wuhan new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters put forward the principle of "every treatment should be received, every treatment should be given" , it is required that the diagnosed patients must be under centralized treatment, the suspected patients must be under centralized isolation, the patients with fever who can not be definitely excluded must be under centralized isolation observation, and the close contacts of the diagnosed patients must be under centralized isolation observation.

At the same time, all over the country to Wuhan chi-aid has never stopped. A total of 9061 members from 96 medical teams are supporting the medical rescue work in Wuhan, according to a news conference on the prevention and control of the new coronavirus epidemic held in Hubei Province on February 6. Eleven medical teams and 1,535 medical personnel were also assigned to 10 municipalities in Huanggang, Ezhou, Xiaogan, Xianning, Jingzhou, Jingmen and Xiangyang, in response to the fact that medical resources in each municipality and state were relatively tight.

Unfortunately, sometimes the phone rings and before you can ask if the problem has been solved, the person says, probably not. Clearly, some of the patients were not outpacing the pace. Some hung up in silence, others cursed in anger.

Early in the morning of February 6, Hao Ming sent me a message: the Local Health Commission told us that the hospital list has been opened, the next day can be hospitalized.

Finally he said, "it's too bad grandma can't wait. "

On the third day, Xu's mother in law, Chen Hui, was finally diagnosed. They were expecting positive nucleic acid test results, but unfortunately, the 60 year old mother in law, still couldn't wait for a bed, xu Min announced the news of her mother-in-law's death in the afternoon in the circle of friends.

So is the good news. On the evening of February 6, Cai Ting shared the good news with me. That day, she spoke to her aunt on the phone. Her voice was as healthy as it had been before chemotherapy. Her sister-in-law, a cancer patient on chemotherapy, appears to have recovered from a severe immune deficiency. At present, the aunt has done a nucleic acid test, the result is negative, if the second test is negative, can be discharged from the hospital, just a week in isolation, can go home.

On the other hand, although Cai Ting's mother is only a highly suspected single Yang patient, according to the latest diagnosis and treatment program, this situation can also be reported to the hospital. On the afternoon of the 6th, in the rain and without a car, she pushed her wheelchair for more than an hour, finally pushing her 69-year-old mother into the hospital.

She returned home, exhausted, ready to rest and return to the fight.

This just in

The shortage of medical supplies and the difficulty of testing and diagnosis are being alleviated.

These days, the Vulcan Mountain, Raytheon Mountain Hospital and shelter have been put into use, intensive treatment of severe, mild patients. Fire Mountain Hospital has been officially admitted to treat patients with newly diagnosed pneumonia since February 4. Today, four days later, the hospital has also been put into use. The first medical team has been stationed in the hospital, and patients will start receiving treatment today. The two special hospitals have a total of 2,500 beds.

Starting from the evening of February 3, medical rescue teams from 20 large-scale Tertiary General Hospitals in 20 provinces were urgently dispatched to Transform 13 stadium and convention and Exhibition Centers in Wuhan into "Shelter Hospitals" , for the treatment of new patients with mild coronary pneumonia. At present, Wuhan Convention and Exhibition Center, Wembley Arena, Wuhan Living Room construction of the three shelter hospitals, gradually put into use.

For some patients with fever due to objective reasons can not be confirmed, it is difficult to get effective isolation and treatment of the situation, Wuhan new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters put forward the principle of "every treatment should be received, every treatment should be given" , it is required that the diagnosed patients must be under centralized treatment, the suspected patients must be under centralized isolation, the patients with fever who can not be definitely excluded must be under centralized isolation observation, and the close contacts of the diagnosed patients must be under centralized isolation observation.

At the same time, all over the country to Wuhan chi-aid has never stopped. A total of 9061 members from 96 medical teams are supporting the medical rescue work in Wuhan, according to a news conference on the prevention and control of the new coronavirus epidemic held in Hubei Province on February 6. Eleven medical teams and 1,535 medical personnel were also assigned to 10 municipalities in Huanggang, Ezhou, Xiaogan, Xianning, Jingzhou, Jingmen and Xiangyang, in response to the fact that medical resources in each municipality and state were relatively tight.
